{
  "stem": "12491.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she was safe for a while with the documents which they have issued to her, just like I was safe for a while with the documents which I was issued by the SS, having worked with that furrier.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Who was wearing them?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, they were for Germans.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was all for Germans.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was for Germans.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Who were the people who run that shop?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On June 6, 1942, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the Germans assembled all the Jews in a plaza, and [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] each one of us had to-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] had to stand in front of a German officer who-- who inspected your identification card and inspected your papers of your work assignment.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they decided whether the work assignment is important for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Therefore, you would be allowed to stay in ghetto and continue or that it's not important with Germans.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Therefore, you will be moved to, as they say, [GERMAN] to another location.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My sister had the-- passed and received a stamp, a special stamp on her identification card indicating that she's allowed to stay in ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So was I.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I got also such a stamp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My mother did not since she had no assignment.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And on the 6th of June, my mother and many hundreds or a couple-- two or three thousand of people-- were taken out of ghetto.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And to best of my knowledge, the whole transport wound up in Belzec, where they were all exterminated.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
